credit_line: Patrons Art Fund
provenance_text:
Luigi Lucioni [1900-1988], New York, NY, until December 1940 [1]; Walker Galleries, New York, NY [2]; purchased by Department of Fine Arts, Carnegie Institute, Pittsburgh, PA, December 1940 [3].

Notes:
[1]. The painting was no. 287 (listed as "Lent by the Artist") in the exhibition "Survey of American Painting" held at Carnegie Institute, October-December, 1940. 
[2]. The gallery acted as agent. See "American Paintings and Sculpture to 1945 in the Carnegie Museum of Art," page 329.
[3]. The museum purchased the painting from the exhibition in Note [1] and accessioned it on December 6, 1940.

title: Portrait of Elderly Jew with Fur Hat
credit_line: Bequest of Charles J. Rosenbloom
provenance_text:
Charles J. Rosenbloom [1898-1973], Pittsburgh, PA (Lugt Suppl. 633b), by February 1946 until April 1, 1973 [1]; bequest to Israel Museum, Jerusalem, Israel; by exchange, Museum of Art, Carnegie Institute, Pittsburgh, PA, February 1975 [2]. 

Notes:
[1]. The painting, as "Head of an Elderly Jew," was included in the exhibition "Paintings and Prints from the Collection of Charles J. Rosenbloom" that was held at the museum in February-March 1946. It was illustrated in the exhibition catalogue.
[2]. Exchanged for "Picnic" by Thomas Hart Benton, also from the Rosenbloom collection.
